“Message delivery in RabbitMQ is ensured using multiple mechanisms: publisher confirms guarantee the broker received the message, durable queues and persistent messages ensure data survives broker restarts, and consumer acknowledgements ensure messages are only removed
after successful processing. In case of failure, messages are re-queued or moved to dead letter queues. This provides at-least-once delivery, and consumers must be idempotent to handle duplicates safely.”

A binding is a relationship + routing rule between an exchange and a queue.
